Exterminate

While druids act in harmony with nature, there are times
when they find themselves in conflict with some of
nature's creatures.  Some druids resolve such conflicts
peacefully; however, some, particularly those druids
more inclined toward evil, choose more violent methods.
This spell is one of those; it calls upon the darker side
of nature in an attempt to eliminate a life force from
the cycle.  It can target only vermin, such as insects,
mice and rats, spiders, and toads.  Higher animals and
humans are immune to its effects, and the life force
of plants is sufficiently different to render them
immune as well.

Command: exterminate <target> (defaults to attacker)
Base Cost: 60 SP
Base Recovery: medium-long
Base Effect: damage (extreme, vermin only)
Base Duration: instant
Guild Level: 3
